class vizasm.model.asm.Register.Register(register, register_dict=None)[source]¶

Bases: object

This class represents an register of the cpu. It implements a fallback support for a register if the register_dict variable is set.

Fallback support means e.g. that “eax” presents the lower 32 bits of “rax” and if the value of “eax” cannot be looked up in the Registers class, all of the fallback registers can be tried.

A Register is equal to another, if they have the same fallback list. If the fallback list is None, the register is used for equality.

Parameters :

register: string :

fallback_list: list<string> :

list of equivalent registers used for fallback support. E.g. on x86_64 ‘rsp’ and ‘esp’ are equal.

Methods

fallback_support(register, register_dict) Returns a list of registers which are equal in the manner that one registers uses the memory space of the other.
